``` Detection: T1219 — Remote Access Software (RMM tool) DNS resolution.

    Production artifact: `rmm_tool_use` macro in this folder's macros.conf.

    Logic: enrich Zeek dns.log with the rmm_domains.csv lookup; suppress
    allow-listed sources via rmm_user_allowlist.csv; aggregate per
    (5-min window, src) and require at least one resolved RMM-tool domain.

    Single-event signal — a host resolving teamviewer.com or anydesk.com
    is noteworthy in any environment that doesn't sanction those tools.
```

index=zeek sourcetype=zeek:dns
| eval query=lower(query)
| where isnotnull(query) AND len(query) > 0
``` Extract base domain (last two labels) ```
| eval _parts=split(query, ".")
| eval n_parts=mvcount(_parts)
| where n_parts >= 2
| eval base_domain=mvindex(_parts, n_parts-2) . "." . mvindex(_parts, n_parts-1)
``` Match against the RMM-domain IOC lookup. Replace the lab list with a
    maintained feed (Red Canary RMM list, vendor cloud-app inventory) in
    production. ```
| lookup rmm_domains.csv domain AS base_domain OUTPUT tool
| where isnotnull(tool)
``` Skip allow-listed sources (help-desk hosts, MSP-managed endpoints) ```
| lookup rmm_user_allowlist.csv src OUTPUT allow
| where isnull(allow) OR allow!="true"
| bin _time span=5m
| stats count                       AS total_queries,
        dc(base_domain)             AS distinct_rmm_domains,
        values(base_domain)         AS domains,
        values(tool)                AS tools
        BY _time, src
| eval sample_domains = mvindex(domains, 0, 4)
``` Threshold — even one resolution is interesting in unsanctioned environments. ```
| where distinct_rmm_domains >= 1
| eval case_id="t1219_rmm_tool_use",
       case_title="Remote Access Software (RMM)",
       mitre_technique="T1219",
       mitre_tactic="command-and-control",
       severity="high"
| sort - distinct_rmm_domains
| table _time, src, distinct_rmm_domains, total_queries, tools, sample_domains, mitre_technique, mitre_tactic, severity, case_id, case_title
